`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The walk bob is additive with the existing sway — both modify the tool's Y position, so they can be combined cleanly in the same `group.position.set()` call.
- The canonical formula `bobHeight * sin(time * bobFrequency) * speed` means: full amplitude when walking at full speed, zero bob when standing still (no need for separate lerp-back logic).
- `bobTimeRef` should accumulate unconditionally every frame (not just when moving), so the phase stays consistent — the speed factor controls amplitude.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
